or more affordable to divert

00:46:03.700 --> 00:46:04.950
the water from somewhere else.

00:46:04.950 --> 00:46:08.320
A place that is not, it's
not safe for the residents.

00:46:08.320 --> 00:46:10.990
So if you can
extrapolate that instance

00:46:10.990 --> 00:46:14.940
into all of the different
ways that the interests

00:46:14.940 --> 00:46:18.000
of private industry might not
be the same as the interests

00:46:18.000 --> 00:46:21.170
of like the public good.

00:46:21.170 --> 00:46:23.960
I don't like to generally
talk in slippery slopes

00:46:23.960 --> 00:46:27.140
but a lot of bad
things could happen.

00:46:27.140 --> 00:46:29.720
So that is I think
something that whether that

00:46:29.720 --> 00:46:34.040
is in education or it's
something that in Southern

00:46:34.040 --> 00:46:35.940
California is
always a hot topic,

00:46:35.940 --> 00:46:37.827
whether that has to
do with our beaches

00:46:37.827 --> 00:46:40.160
our state beaches which we
have miles and miles of miles

00:46:40.160 --> 00:46:42.326
of that people are always
trying to get a referendum

00:46:42.326 --> 00:46:44.870
on a local ballot to change.

00:46:44.870 --> 00:46:47.180
What does that mean
for future generations?

00:46:47.180 --> 00:46:49.400
That is something that we
all have to think about.

00:46:49.400 --> 00:46:51.200
And we all have to
vote accordingly

00:46:51.200 --> 00:46:52.970
to the conclusions we come to.

00:46:52.970 --> 00:46:59.970
Because it is something that
is really under fire right now.

00:46:59.970 --> 00:47:04.080
- My name is Joseph Greenberg.

00:47:04.080 --> 00:47:08.430
I'm a graduate of the college
and a native of Cambridge.

00:47:08.430 --> 00:47:13.280
And I was particularly
struck by the question

00:47:13.280 --> 00:47:19.940
that you ended with, with
regards to development,

00:47:19.940 --> 00:47:25.842
whether or not
existing residents feel

00:47:25.842 --> 00:47:32.960
a part of new developments or
if they feel excluded by it.

00:47:32.960 --> 00:47:39.170
My question is really
how do cities engage

00:47:39.170 --> 00:47:46.060
with the people who will be most
impacted by the decision making

00:47:46.060 --> 00:47:50.480
process that are usually
excluded from it.

00:47:50.480 --> 00:47:55.330
For example, I was at the
Cambridge Board of this Zoning

00:47:55.330 --> 00:48:04.630
Appeals hearing last night and
I was the youngest person there.

00:48:04.630 --> 00:48:11.650
The crowd skewed very
older and whiter.

00:48:11.650 --> 00:48:16.390
And it just seems to me that
decisions at this kind of level

00:48:16.390 --> 00:48:19.260
are being made without
input from the people who

00:48:19.260 --> 00:48:24.430
will be most affected by it.

00:48:24.430 --> 00:48:32.320
So how do cities facilitate
a more inclusive conversation

00:48:32.320 --> 00:48:38.769
around new developments.

00:48:38.769 --> 00:48:40.310
- That's a very good
question Joseph.

00:48:40.310 --> 00:48:44.677
So I think there's
like a quick answer

00:48:44.677 --> 00:48:45.760
and there's a long answer.

00:48:45.760 --> 00:48:49.620
So the quick answer
is just do better.

00:48:49.620 --> 00:48:52.030
If it's your job to get
people to come to a thing,

00:48:52.030 --> 00:48:53.980
whether you're a party
promoter or you're

00:48:53.980 --> 00:48:55.510
putting on a
conference, you need

00:48:55.510 --> 00:48:58.010
to figure out how to reach the
people that need to be there.

00:48:58.010 --> 00:49:00.430
And so for them to
say, well, we posted it

00:49:00.430 --> 00:49:04.960
in the community newsletter and
that was that, it is your job.

00:49:04.960 --> 00:49:07.540
If that is what your charge
is, to engage that community,

00:49:07.540 --> 00:49:10.730
you need to figure out how
to engage that community.

00:49:10.730 --> 00:49:14.980
And the long answer
is that also it

00:49:14.980 --> 00:49:18.220
has so much to do with
so many levels of just

00:49:18.220 --> 00:49:19.580
institutionalized exclusion.

00:49:19.580 --> 00:49:23.020
So if you have the people
who are putting on the zoning

00:49:23.020 --> 00:49:26.890
