00:50:02.470 --> 00:50:04.484
It's easy to say they
need to figure out a way

00:50:04.484 --> 00:50:05.650
to outreach to these people.

00:50:05.650 --> 00:50:08.260
But they have to do the
work, a lot of the work

00:50:08.260 --> 00:50:11.470
that people don't
want to do earlier.

00:50:11.470 --> 00:50:13.960
If this is the population
I serve, why doesn't anyone

00:50:13.960 --> 00:50:16.600
on this board look
like this population.

00:50:16.600 --> 00:50:17.320
Thank you.

00:50:17.320 --> 00:50:22.252
- Thank you very much

00:50:22.252 --> 00:50:23.070
- Hi, I'm Chris.

00:50:23.070 --> 00:50:24.903
Thank you very much for
your insightful talk

00:50:24.903 --> 00:50:27.120
I'll have to read the book now.

00:50:27.120 --> 00:50:29.850
So my question, I
worked for a publication

00:50:29.850 --> 00:50:33.900
that covers data driven
policy, the use of data

00:50:33.900 --> 00:50:39.180
to inform those residents to
serve and how to serve them.

00:50:39.180 --> 00:50:40.660
And it seems like
the work you do,

00:50:40.660 --> 00:50:42.210
writing fiction
can inform policy

00:50:42.210 --> 00:50:45.000
in a much more personal way.

00:50:45.000 --> 00:50:50.370
So I'm sort of wondering how
you think things like fiction

00:50:50.370 --> 00:50:52.710
could be integrated
into policy and how

00:50:52.710 --> 00:50:55.380
to balance the personal
connection to residents

00:50:55.380 --> 00:50:59.220
or a city with things like
data that can inform policy.

00:51:01.730 --> 00:51:04.250
- Well you know a fiction
writer doesn't ever

00:51:04.250 --> 00:51:06.380
think their writing
is useful for anything

00:51:06.380 --> 00:51:10.580
besides hopefully getting
people to turn the next page.

00:51:10.580 --> 00:51:13.100
But I appreciate you saying so.

00:51:13.100 --> 00:51:19.000
I think that one of the things
that I try to do in my fiction

00:51:19.000 --> 00:51:20.160
is--

00:51:20.160 --> 00:51:22.130
and that's because I
write realist fiction,

00:51:22.130 --> 00:51:24.170
even though full
disclosure there's

00:51:24.170 --> 00:51:26.060
a there's a ghost in
this book in the novel

00:51:26.060 --> 00:51:28.190
so don't be alarmed
there's a ghost,

00:51:28.190 --> 00:51:31.010
but it's still realist in my
opinion like realist fiction--

00:51:31.010 --> 00:51:36.230
is that I really don't
try to have the answer.

00:51:36.230 --> 00:51:38.780
I write books to answer
questions for myself.

00:51:38.780 --> 00:51:41.392
So I have a question when
I begin to write a book

00:51:41.392 --> 00:51:42.600
or I begin to write anything.

00:51:42.600 --> 00:51:43.970
I don't have the answer.

00:51:43.970 --> 00:51:46.850
And that is why
if people do think

00:51:46.850 --> 00:51:50.780
that my book is like a good
portrait of the city of Detroit

00:51:50.780 --> 00:51:53.420
over this many years
is because I was trying

00:51:53.420 --> 00:51:56.750
to answer the question of why
is the house that my father grew

00:51:56.750 --> 00:51:59.960
up in, why is it in
the state that it's in.

00:51:59.960 --> 00:52:01.040
What does that mean?

00:52:01.040 --> 00:52:02.530
And how do people feel about it?

00:52:02.530 --> 00:52:04.700
And so because my
brain is not one

00:52:04.700 --> 00:52:07.970
that was really interested
in synthesizing data

00:52:07.970 --> 00:52:10.880
to just deliver it, I'm
interested in synthesizing data

00:52:10.880 --> 00:52:12.710
to make a story.

00:52:12.710 --> 00:52:15.620
I still go through some of
the same methods of inquiry.

00:52:15.620 --> 00:52:16.680
They're not as linear.

00:52:16.680 --> 00:52:17.680
They're a little sloppy.

00:52:17.680 --> 00:52:19.310
They're hard to
explain to people.

00:52:19.310 --> 00:52:24.860
But I think that one
thing that perhaps having

00:52:24.860 --> 00:52:28.880
some more creative people be
part of that conversation can

00:52:28.880 --> 00:52:34.430
do is get to that same point
of inquiry and exploration

00:52:34.430 --> 00:52:37.130
without a preconceived idea.

00:52:37.130 --> 00:52:41.210
I did not have a
million ideas about what

00:52:41.210 --> 00:52:44.540
had happened to make
the city of Detroit

00:52:44.540 --> 00:52:46.850
and the place my father
grew up the way that it was.

00:52:46.850 --> 00:52:48.225
I had a few ideas.

00:52:48.225 --> 00:52:50.850
And I actually found out that a
lot of those were not accurate.

00:52:50.850 --> 00:52:52.779
I thought it was
really just cars.

00:52:52.779 --> 00:52:54.320
They stopped making
cars in the city.

00:52:54.320 --> 00:52:56.069
And so there was nothing
left in the city.

00:52:56.069 --> 00:52:56.930
And that's not true.

00:52:56.930 --> 00:52:58.310
When they were
still making cars,

00:52:58.310 --> 00:53:00.410
the seeds were already
sown for the city

00:53:00.410 --> 00:53:01.500
to end up where it was.

00:53:01.500 --> 00:53:03.920
And so that's something
that if I was determined

00:53:03.920 --> 00:53:05.520
to have my answer
be the correct one,

00:53:05.520 --> 00:53:08.900
I would have never
even been receptive

00:53:08.900 --> 00:53:10.303
to that other information.

00:53:10.303 --> 00:53:11.010
- Thank you.

